<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Projects | Josiah Tayi</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
<header>
    <span class="nav-logo">Josiah <span>Tayi</span></span>
    <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/projects" class="active">Projects</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
    </nav>
</header>

<main class="projects-page">
    <section class="projects-intro">
        <h2>Projects</h2>
        <p>Production web applications and personal projects I've designed, built, and shipped end-to-end.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="project-filters">
        <h3>Filter by:</h3>
        <div class="filter-buttons">
            <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
            <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="web">Web Development</button>
            <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="personal">Personal</button>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="projects-grid">

        <article class="project-card" data-category="web">
            <div class="project-banner banner-1">FinSeeker</div>
            <div class="project-content">
                <h3>FinSeeker.com.au</h3>
                <div class="project-tags">
                    <span class="tag">Next.js 15</span>
                    <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
                    <span class="tag">Supabase</span>
                    <span class="tag">Drizzle ORM</span>
                    <span class="tag">Stripe</span>
                </div>
                <p class="project-description">B2B commercial-lending matchmaking platform connecting Australian finance seekers (brokers, accountants, CFOs) with lender BDMs. Seekers post funding requests anonymously; lenders pitch with indicative rates and terms.</p>
                <div class="project-features">
                    <h4>Key Features</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Dual-portal architecture with role-based auth via Better Auth and magic-link email flows</li>
                        <li>Supabase Realtime live chat — deal qualification before identity disclosure</li>
                        <li>Stripe subscription &amp; credit-purchase system with webhook lifecycle handling</li>
                        <li>Transactional emails via Resend across 15+ commercial finance categories</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-links">
                    <a href="https://finseeker.com.au" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">Visit Site</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="project-card" data-category="web">
            <div class="project-banner banner-2">Quiz Builder</div>
            <div class="project-content">
                <h3>Vision Verse Quiz Builder</h3>
                <div class="project-tags">
                    <span class="tag">Next.js</span>
                    <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
                    <span class="tag">PostgreSQL</span>
                    <span class="tag">Clerk</span>
                    <span class="tag">Recharts</span>
                </div>
                <p class="project-description">Full-stack quiz creation and analytics platform built at Vision Verse Interactive. Supports drag-and-drop quiz building, multiple scoring systems, and shareable links with no participant registration required.</p>
                <div class="project-features">
                    <h4>Key Features</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Drag-and-drop builder with reusable page templates (onboarding, quiz, results)</li>
                        <li>JSONB-based PostgreSQL schema with draft/publish versioning via Drizzle ORM</li>
                        <li>Real-time analytics dashboard — device breakdowns, response data, performance</li>
                        <li>Google OAuth via Clerk; media uploads (images/GIFs) via UploadThing</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-links">
                    <a href="https://github.com/gpaa487/visionverse" target="_blank" class="btn">GitHub</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="project-card" data-category="web personal">
            <div class="project-banner banner-4">What Josiah Watched</div>
            <div class="project-content">
                <h3>What Josiah Watched</h3>
                <div class="project-tags">
                    <span class="tag">Next.js</span>
                    <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
                    <span class="tag">MongoDB</span>
                    <span class="tag">TMDB API</span>
                    <span class="tag">Tailwind CSS</span>
                </div>
                <p class="project-description">Full-stack horror-film curation app with a cinematic admin dashboard for managing a personal watch history, auto-enriched with cast, director, poster, and runtime data via the TMDB API.</p>
                <div class="project-features">
                    <h4>Key Features</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Real-time TMDB discovery — "Now in Cinemas" homepage &amp; "More Like This" on detail pages</li>
                        <li>TypeScript bulk-import script with metadata enrichment and duplicate detection from CSV</li>
                        <li>Secure admin interface with featured-film scheduling and watch-history tracking</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-links">
                    <a href="https://whatjosiahwatched.vercel.app" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">Visit Site</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="project-card" data-category="personal">
            <div class="project-banner banner-5">Home Lab</div>
            <div class="project-content">
                <h3>Self-Hosted Home Infrastructure</h3>
                <div class="project-tags">
                    <span class="tag">Linux</span>
                    <span class="tag">Docker</span>
                    <span class="tag">Tailscale</span>
                    <span class="tag">Networking</span>
                </div>
                <p class="project-description">Self-hosted media server and home network designed and maintained on Linux, demonstrating practical DevOps, networking, and containerisation skills.</p>
                <div class="project-features">
                    <h4>Key Features</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Docker containers for service isolation and easy management</li>
                        <li>VLAN segmentation for network security</li>
                        <li>Secure remote access via Tailscale VPN</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

    </section>

    <section class="collaboration">
        <h2>Interested in Collaborating?</h2>
        <p>I'm always open to working on interesting projects with other developers. If you have an idea you'd like to build together, feel free to reach out.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn primary-btn">Contact Me</a>
    </section>
</main>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2025 Josiah Tayi</p>
    <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
    </div>
</footer>

<script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
        const filterBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn');
        const projectCards = document.querySelectorAll('.project-card');

        filterBtns.forEach(btn => {
            btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
                filterBtns.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
                this.classList.add('active');
                const filter = this.getAttribute('data-filter');
                projectCards.forEach(card => {
                    if (filter === 'all') {
                        card.style.display = 'flex';
                    } else {
                        const cats = card.getAttribute('data-category').split(' ');
                        card.style.display = cats.includes(filter) ? 'flex' : 'none';
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    });
</script>
</body>
</html>
